IMP is a library, standing for nothing in particular, except when you link against it it comes out -limp.  It will be the core library of the zde project, containing basic features needed for software development. Possible features are Logging functions, Linked Lists, Hash functions, malloc/free wrappers, Berkely DB wrappers, sorting functions, searching functions, string manipulation functions, simple encryption and compression functions, stacks & queues, and trees.  Since it will be written in Objective-C, one of its primary features will be also be an Object hierarchy and releated functions.
